eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.

If BRAFV600-mutant, documented refractory disease to at least one BRAF inhibitor (dabrafenib or vemurafenib) and/or a MEK inhibitor (trametinib or combimetinib), defined as progression of measurable disease as per Response Evaluation Criteria in Solid Tumors (RECIST) criteria while on treatment

Impaired gastrointestinal function or poorly controlled gastrointestinal disease that may significantly alter the absorption of oral BYL719 (e.g. Crohn's disease, ulcerative colitis, malabsorption syndrome, small bowel resection, uncontrolled nausea or vomiting, or grade >= 3 diarrhea of any etiology) based on treating physician assessment
Have a Distress Thermometer score of 4 or greater or a score of >= 6 on the Depression or Anxiety subscale of the Hospital Anxiety and Depression Scale (HADS)
Anticipated life expectancy of at least 12 weeks

groups.description: Patients undergo supervised aerobic exercise over 40 minutes and resistance training over 20 minutes 3 times per week for 20 weeks. Patients then participate in regular exercise sessions on flexible schedule for 32 weeks.
groups.name: Group I (exercise physical activity intervention)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: 100-day NRM rate will be compared to the 100-day NRM rate in the initial TJU 2 step trial and similar trials reported in the literature. The null hypothesis is that the true rate of 100 day NRM is 30% or higher. The alternative hypothesis is that this rate is lower than 30%. The primary hypothesis will be tested using a one-sided exact binomial hypothesis test for the single proportion with alpha=0.05. The sample size of 45 patients provides 82% power to reject the null hypothesis if the true NRM rate is 14% and 91% power if the true NRM rate is 12%.
outcome_measures.measure: 100-day NRM rate, defined as death from GVHD, infection, or regimen-related toxicity from day 0 to day 100 post HSCT (Phase II)
